            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I guess what I'm looking for is a way of configuring the diagnostic floating window and its buffer.\n\n## Full story,\n\nThe default LSP diagnostic output looks as follows for a somewhat simple object.\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/68ef3ef7-f0ab-4384-a8b5-929850803462)\n\nI used a custom formatter to parse the diagnostic error message and prettify the error as follows. I used markdown syntax as the output of format function assuming that diagnostic floating window is customizable. My original plan was to output markdown content and somehow set the file type of the floating window to `markdown` so that I get syntax highlighting and stuff.\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/19ff3b75-948f-499a-8bf2-f77c9ae87b35)\n\nHere I add the custom formatter\n\nhttps://github.com/s1n7ax/lazyvim-dotnvim/blob/e019aa2d5d435be2e12e8908cc864337bc84952f/lua/config/options.lua?plain=1#L17-L24\n\nHere is how I parse the diagnostic. I only parse diagnostics that are coming from `ts` and parse only known diagnostic codes. If something goes wrong, I fallback to the default message.\n\nhttps://github.com/s1n7ax/lazyvim-dotnvim/blob/e019aa2d5d435be2e12e8908cc864337bc84952f/lua/utils/lsp/diagnostic/format.lua#L35-L57",
