            "body": "@justinmk No. That's what I thought initially. I thought I could do following\n\n```lua\nvim.diagnostic.config({\n  virtual_text = false,\n  float = function()\n    local bufnr = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\n    vim.bo[bufnr].filetype = 'markdown'\n\n    return {\n      bufnr = bufnr\n    }\n  end,\n})\n```\n\nBut that bufnr is just the current buffer of the file not the floating window. It's replaced here\n\nhttps://github.com/s1n7ax/neovim/blob/a78eddd54112033eea0212865efd2f75cc59fc93/runtime/lua/vim/diagnostic.lua?plain=1#L1024-L1030",
